❯ do I need to run this on the A100 still or can I switch over to a t4          

⏺ Switch to T4 — everything left is cheap.

  What's remaining and its compute profile:
  - Downloads (sub-02..sub-05, ~21 GB): pure I/O, GPU doesn't matter
  - Variant A (zero-shot): model.eval() on 200 test samples — milliseconds
  - Variant B (subject-block FT): encoder is frozen, only training a (384×3200)
  head — ~1-2 min/subject on T4
  - Variant C (full FT, 1 epoch): this is the slowest piece — ~5-10 min/subject
  on T4 vs ~1 min on A100. Across 5 subjects: ~30-50 min on T4 vs ~5 min on
  A100. Still very tractable.
  - Phase 7e figure + Phase 8 report: CPU only

  The only thing that was expensive (Phase 5 multi-subject training, 30 epochs
  each) is already done — those checkpoints are on Drive.

  Stopping the A100 here is safe. Switch to T4.

  Heads-up: when the kernel restarts on hardware switch, /content/work/ is wiped
   and in-memory variables are gone. After switching I'll need to re-run a few
